 {"id":"frankenpandas-qs9u","title":"fd90.83: README claims 17 output methods but table lists 12","description":"Self-review: README line 491 'DataFrame Output Formats' section claims '17 output methods' but the table beneath lists only 12 methods (to_csv / to_json / to_string_table / to_string_truncated / to_html / to_latex / to_markdown / to_dict / to_series_dict / to_records / to_numpy_2d / Display trait). The 17 figure appears to count fp-io's DataFrameIoExt methods (11 of them: to_parquet, to_parquet_bytes, to_csv_file, to_json_file, to_excel_file, to_excel_bytes, to_jsonl_file, to_feather_file, to_feather_bytes, to_sql, to_sql_with_options) but those aren't in the table either. Either way 17 doesn't match what users see. Fix: replace the count with an accurate breakdown - the table has 12 inline DataFrame output methods plus the fp-io DataFrameIoExt extension trait adds 11 more file/bytes IO writers. Pure README change, no code impact.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"docs","assignee":"cc-pandas-2","created_at":"2026-04-26T08:20:07.302262726Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T08:22:03.648049060Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T08:22:03.644991600Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["docs","fd90","readme","review"]}
